# Turkish → ASCII-Latin transliteration rules (tr_lat.rules)
#
# Sources:
#   - Arslan, A. (2016). "DeASCIIfication approach to handle diacritics in Turkish information retrieval".
#     Information Processing & Management, 52(2): 326-339.
#     DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ipm.2015.08.004
#
#   - Torunoğlu, D. & Eryiğit, G. (2014). "A Cascaded Approach for Social Media Text Normalization of Turkish".
#     Proceedings of the 5th Workshop on Language Analysis for Social Media (LASM), pp. 62-70.
#
# One-to-one, case-preserving fold of Turkish diacritic letters to plain Latin;
# all other ASCII letters map to themselves.

Ç > C ;  ç > c ;
Ğ > G ;  ğ > g ;
İ > I ;  i > i ;   # dotted I/i keep ASCII shape
I > I ;  ı > i ;   # dotless ı becomes ASCII i
Ö > O ;  ö > o ;
Ş > S ;  ş > s ;
Ü > U ;  ü > u ;

